node.text: @loveeveryday 😂🤣 u are absolutely right! Yes yes!
@loveeveryday primary sch kids r playing w them actually. I think as long they can understand instructions,  cos it's very easy to follow.

I was asking some parents for recommendations and here’s a list suitable for primary sch age kiddos...
. ✅Sushi Go Party
✅Counting Mountains
✅Connect 4
✅Cluedo
✅Operation
✅Go Fish
✅ Where Are You?
✅Othello
✅Snakes and Ladders
✅Ticket to Ride
✅Monopoly
✅Organ Attack
✅Taboo
✅Uno
✅Boggle
✅Game of Life
✅Simon’s Cat
✅Scrabble
.
Wow there are some games which I’ve never heard of! If you have other fun games to add on, let me know. If it has an educational element, even better 😂.
.
Side note: I have to referee every game if not my boys will end up cheating and then fighting, very competitive at home 😅.
.
